! SUSP_X: Wheel longitudinal (X) as a function of jounce (Z). X movement is a
! function of jounce (CONSTANT, COEFFICIENT, or TABLE). X movement from the
! calculation can be adjusted with SUSP_X_GAIN and SUSP_X_OFFSET. Jounce used in the
! calculation can be adjusted with JNC_SCALE_SUSP_X and JNC_START_SUSP_X. The
! derivative of this function is used internally. This configurable function supports
! 2 datasets; if indices shown below are not used, e.g., (2), the current value of
! the index IAXLE is used to identify the dataset when reading data.

! Col 1 = jounce (mm), col 2 = x movement (mm)
SUSP_X_TABLE(1) SPLINE ! spline interpolation and extrapolation
 -30, -5.51051
 -28, -6.83489
 -26, -7.47926
 -24, -7.70724
 -22, -7.65204
 -20, -7.39445
